Portfolio Documentation: https://confluence.atlassian.com/jiraportfolioserver/scheduling-settings-715263133.html
{quote}This setting controls whether a dependant story can be scheduled within the same sprint. By default, the setting is "Off" so that dependant stories will be placed in subsequent sprints. When 'On', stories with dependencies can be scheduled within the same sprint if there is available capacity.{quote}

In Portfolio configuration page itself:
{quote}If set to 'On', work items with dependencies cannot be worked on concurrently. For Scrum teams, they will be scheduled in separate sprints. For Kanban teams, they'll be scheduled on separate days. If this option is disabled, work items with dependencies can be worked on at the same time. In both cases the dependent work items can never start before their predecessors.{quote}

The description in the Portfolio configuration page is better and covers both Kanban/Scrum. The description in the documentation should be replaced with the description from configuration page.

